<subsection><title>Example 2: <tag>row</tag> with multiple position and alignment attributes</title>
<p>In the code below, the <attr>left</attr>, <attr>bottom</attr>, <attr>valign</attr> and <attr>halign</attr> attributes are used with the <tag>row</tag> component.  Valid values for the <attr>valign</attr> attribute are: <c>"top", "middle"</c> and <c>"right"</c> and the default value is <c>"middle"</c>. Valid values for the <attr>halign</attr> attribute are: <c>"left", "center", "justify",</c> and <c>"right"</c> and the default value is <c>"left"</c>.  If an attribute is specified in both a parent and a child component, the styling specified by the child component governs. (See also, <ref uri="doenet:doenetId=zRuXlzQ0_iNqNqZHHQMxG"><tag>table</tag></ref>, <ref uri="doenet:doenetId=5HERf7liZuJ_-NnhzeTaU"><tag>title</tag></ref>.)</p>
<example boxed="true"><title>Sample DoenetML code (Example 2)</title>  
<pre>
&lt;table&gt;&lt;title&gt;Nonsense emoji shuffle&lt;/title&gt;
  &lt;tabular width="500" height="300" bottom="medium" top="medium" left="medium" right="medium"&gt;
    &lt;row halign="center" bottom="minor"&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🔴&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🔵&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🟢&lt;/cell&gt;
    &lt;/row&gt;
    
    &lt;row  halign="right" bottom="minor"&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🟢&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🟣&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🔵&lt;/cell&gt;
    &lt;/row&gt;
    
    &lt;row valign="top" left="minor"&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🟠&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🔴&lt;/cell&gt;
      &lt;cell&gt;🟣&lt;/cell&gt;
    &lt;/row&gt;
  &lt;/tabular&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

</pre>
  </example>
</subsection>

<!--*******************************************************-->
 
<example><title>What Doenet Renders (Example 2)</title>
<table><title>Nonsense emoji shuffle</title>
  <tabular width="500" height="300" bottom="medium" top="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
    <row halign="center" bottom="minor">
